modules.name: AWS.AppStream
modules.comments:
Amazon AppStream 2.0

You can use Amazon AppStream 2.0 to stream desktop applications to any device running a web browser, without rewriting them.

declarations.comments: Associates the specified fleet with the specified stack.
declarations.title: associateFleet

declarations.comments: Copies the image within the same region or to a new region within the same AWS account. Note that any tags you added to the image will not be copied.
declarations.title: copyImage

declarations.comments:
Creates an image builder.

The initial state of the builder is PENDING. When it is ready, the state is RUNNING.
declarations.title: createImageBuilder

declarations.comments: Creates a URL to start an image builder streaming session.
declarations.title: createImageBuilderStreamingURL

declarations.comments: Creates a URL to start a streaming session for the specified user.
declarations.title: createStreamingURL

declarations.comments: Deletes the specified image. You cannot delete an image that is currently in use. After you delete an image, you cannot provision new capacity using the image.
declarations.title: deleteImage

declarations.comments: Deletes the specified image builder and releases the capacity.
declarations.title: deleteImageBuilder

declarations.comments: Deletes the specified stack. After this operation completes, the environment can no longer be activated and any reservations made for the stack are released.
declarations.title: deleteStack

declarations.comments: Describes the specified directory configurations. Note that although the response syntax in this topic includes the account password, this password is not returned in the actual response.
declarations.title: describeDirectoryConfigs

declarations.comments: Describes the specified fleets or all fleets in the account.
declarations.title: describeFleets

declarations.comments: Describes the specified image builders or all image builders in the account.
declarations.title: describeImageBuilders

declarations.comments: Describes the specified images or all images in the account.
declarations.title: describeImages

declarations.comments: Describes the streaming sessions for the specified stack and fleet. If a user ID is provided, only the streaming sessions for only that user are returned. If an authentication type is not provided, the default is to authenticate users using a streaming URL.
declarations.title: describeSessions

declarations.comments: Describes the specified stacks or all stacks in the account.
declarations.title: describeStacks

declarations.comments: Disassociates the specified fleet from the specified stack.
declarations.title: disassociateFleet

declarations.comments: Lists the fleets associated with the specified stack.
declarations.title: listAssociatedFleets

declarations.comments: Lists the stacks associated with the specified fleet.
declarations.title: listAssociatedStacks

declarations.comments:
Lists the tags for the specified AppStream 2.0 resource. You can tag AppStream 2.0 image builders, images, fleets, and stacks.

For more information about tags, see Tagging Your Resources in the Amazon AppStream 2.0 Developer Guide.
declarations.title: listTagsForResource

declarations.comments:
Adds or overwrites one or more tags for the specified AppStream 2.0 resource. You can tag AppStream 2.0 image builders, images, fleets, and stacks.

Each tag consists of a key and an optional value. If a resource already has a tag with the same key, this operation updates its value.

To list the current tags for your resources, use ListTagsForResource. To disassociate tags from your resources, use UntagResource.

For more information about tags, see Tagging Your Resources in the Amazon AppStream 2.0 Developer Guide.
declarations.title: tagResource

declarations.comments:
Disassociates the specified tags from the specified AppStream 2.0 resource.

To list the current tags for your resources, use ListTagsForResource.

For more information about tags, see Tagging Your Resources in the Amazon AppStream 2.0 Developer Guide.
declarations.title: untagResource

declarations.comments:
Updates the specified fleet.

If the fleet is in the STOPPED state, you can update any attribute except the fleet name. If the fleet is in the RUNNING state, you can update the DisplayName and ComputeCapacity attributes. If the fleet is in the STARTING or STOPPING state, you can't update it.
declarations.title: updateFleet

declarations.comments: Describes an application in the application catalog.
declarations.title: Application

declarations.comments: Describes the capacity status for a fleet.
declarations.title: ComputeCapacityStatus

declarations.comments: An API error occurred. Wait a few minutes and try again.
declarations.title: ConcurrentModificationException

declarations.comments: Configuration information for the directory used to join domains.
declarations.title: DirectoryConfig

declarations.comments: Contains the information needed to join a Microsoft Active Directory domain.
declarations.title: DomainJoinInfo

declarations.comments: Describes a streaming instance used for editing an image. New images are created from a snapshot through an image builder.
declarations.title: ImageBuilder

declarations.comments: Describes the reason why the last image builder state change occurred.
declarations.title: ImageBuilderStateChangeReason

declarations.comments: Describes the reason why the last image state change occurred.
declarations.title: ImageStateChangeReason

declarations.comments: The image does not support storage connectors.
declarations.title: IncompatibleImageException

declarations.comments: Indicates an incorrect combination of parameters, or a missing parameter.
declarations.title: InvalidParameterCombinationException

declarations.comments: The requested limit exceeds the permitted limit for an account.
declarations.title: LimitExceededException

declarations.comments: The specified resource exists and is not in use, but isn't available.
declarations.title: ResourceNotAvailableException

declarations.comments: Describes the credentials for the service account used by the streaming instance to connect to the directory.
declarations.title: ServiceAccountCredentials

declarations.comments: Possible values for the state of a streaming session.
declarations.title: SessionState
